caption: We ordered cocktails and food. The cocktails took over 30 minutes to arrive (and our drinks came after other tables who arrived after us - note that the restaurant was not crowded either) and the food never did, despite informing the waiter. No apology. I love supporting local businesses but I would not go back here. There are other great establishments in the Heights with awesome customer service and excellent food and drinks. I've ordered from this restaurant in grubhub but I must leave a review here as well. Food tastes delicious!! I recommend the fettuccine alfredo with chicken. I recently tried their lobster ravioli and I also must recommend this!! Like real lobster in this and also in the sauce. Their garlic bread is great as well. Instead I'll just say, if you've ever tasted a flake of seasoning, if you have a palette strong enough to withstand, lets say, a sparkling cup of water, than I would pass on this restaurant. I also tried the crab cake, as a joke since I'm from Baltimore. Needless to say the joke was truly on my taste buds, then immediately thereafter, the trash can. I'd avoid it all.

Went here on a Friday night after having the place recommended. Upon walking in I was introduced to club level music volumes.  Sat down and didn't wait to long for service which was nice.  I wouldn't come if you're only in town for a few days and looking to catch up with family or friends due to the music volume.  I had the AquaMojito, figured if they named it after the places it would be a nice signature drink. I wasn't expecting mojito based on the ingredients involved, and I was not disappointed with my assessment. That said, I was expecting something that tasted good. I was disappointed with this assessment. Good amount of alcohol, but the flavors didn't work in a way to make a nice drink.  Starting with the food, the party of 4 I was with ordered dinner, no appetizers. We had two chicken scarpariellos, one veal parm, with a switch to vodka sauce rather than marinara, and one linguine with mushroom dish.  Starting with the chicken scarpariellos... I've never had it without being to taste any tangy flavor, such as lemon, in it. And I've never had it with potatoes, which the menu did mention, but was odd since it came with pasta as well.  My chicken was overcooked like crazy and dry. The other was cooked well enough to be ok. Pasta for both was done garlic and oil sauce. Nothing special. Not bad. Just mediocre  The person with the mushroom dish was happy with it all around.  The person with the veal ran into some problems. After requesting vodka as a switch for marinara we were informed that's an upcharge. We verified that was fine.   The waiter checked that the switch was both for the veal and the separate pasta. The patron verified yes it was. So begins the breakdown. The veal came out with marinara instead. Waiter argued that he asked and was told the vodka was only for the pasta. Which I feel if the music wasn't set to 11 he might have heard correctly since the whole tabled affirmed the person had asked, and verified, to have the sauce switched on both. I heard no offer to refire it from the waiter after this was pointed out. (Edit, I was informed by someone sitting closer he did ask and the diner declined so as not to hold up dinner. I just couldn't hear over the atmosphere)He just argued that it was only for the pasta.  That said the dish was cooked well.  General checkup on the table to top off drinks was average.  Time to wait for them to come back to check if we wanted the check was a bit longer than average.  The last surprises of disappointment of the experience was when we received the check. $3 to switch to the vodka sauce seemed a bit much. It was expected since the waiter mentioned it though. I did wonder if it would have been $6 if it had been swapped on the veal as requested.  And seeing an included gratuity on the bill for a party of 4 caught me like a ball upside the head out of left field since at no point was it mentioned or printed anywhere. No additional tip was left since they reaped the amount they felt due.  All told 2/5. Wouldn't recommend or return. I've been to better Italian, or even fusion, places in NYC.  I'll find another one next time.
